        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-12-20T23:26:42.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Nice to hear, I really appreciate the Roty wines and the family behind them. One wine I really want to taste for my 1980 retrospective is their Charmes-Chambertin, but thus far, no luck. I have only been able to find the Gevrey AOC, which is still showing very well indeed. Roty + challenging vintage + patience is often a winning combination.</p>",
