        "id": 3052226,
        "name": "Asger L a r s e n",
        "username": "Asger_L_a_r_s_e_n",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/asger_l_a_r_s_e_n/{size}/3592_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-12-21T11:56:23.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Thanks for the nice notes</p>\n<p>Really like both Roty and Moine - have a bit in the cellar as well.</p>\n<p>I have some 2013 Roty e.g. Gevrey vv, but have not tried any yet. normally they need a lot cellar time, even Roty Bourgogne rouge and gevrey 1990 was still going strong when I had a couple of years ago. I am currently drinking Bourgogne 1999 with great pleasure.</p>\n<p>I have had the 2013 Moine Vaucrains actually - a couple of times, and have a good amount stored. And also enjoy it very much already now (as with chambolle charmes and clos de la roche 2013). I have never had any Moine with age so it will be interesting to see how it develops over time.</p>",
