        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"166592\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Nice to hear, I really appreciate the Roty wines and the family behind them. One wine I really want to taste for my 1980 retrospective is their Charmes-Chambertin, but thus far, no luck. I have only been able to find the Gevrey AOC, which is still showing very well indeed. Roty + challenging vintage + patience is often a winning combination.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Agreed William, Roty is one of the answers to the question about which producer{s} to go with when the vintage is off.   I wish you good fortune in finding the the 80` retro Charmes.</p>",
